WEBVTT

00:02.500 --> 00:04.166
I KEEP TELLING YOU,
I'M FINE.

00:04.166 --> 00:06.500
DO PEOPLE
WHO ARE FINE SPEND
THE ENTIRE AFTERNOON

00:06.500 --> 00:08.083
IN OUR BATHROOM
THROWING UP?

00:08.083 --> 00:09.333
BUT I'M FINE NOW.

00:09.333 --> 00:12.166
MOM. I'M NOT
TAKING SIDES,
BUT DAD'S RIGHT.

00:12.166 --> 00:13.166
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO GET BETTER

00:13.166 --> 00:14.250
UNLESS YOU GET
SOME REST.

00:14.250 --> 00:17.125
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.
MY OWN SON.

00:19.375 --> 00:22.333
GALE,
THE GUINNESS TAP
JUST RAN DRY,

00:22.333 --> 00:23.417
WE'RE OUT OF
STOLI,

00:23.417 --> 00:24.542
AND SOMEBODY
JUST FOUND

00:24.542 --> 00:25.834
A HAIR
IN THE PRETZELS.

00:25.834 --> 00:28.166
OK. CALL THE BEER DISTRIBUTOR.
TELL HIM HE'S A WEEK LATE.

00:28.166 --> 00:30.041
IF HE CAN'T GET HIS ASS
OVER TODAY, HE'S FIRED.

00:30.041 --> 00:31.708
GIVE THE GUY WHO FOUND A HAIR
A FREE DRINK.

00:31.708 --> 00:34.208
PUT OUT
A FRESH BOWL OF PRETZELS
AND THEN TELL MY HUSBAND

00:34.208 --> 00:36.500
AND MY TRAITOR SON
TO GET OFF MY BACK.

00:36.500 --> 00:37.917
YOU HEARD
THE WOMAN.

00:40.458 --> 00:42.375
FOR THE SAKE OF
YOUR BUSINESS GO HOME

00:42.375 --> 00:44.208
BEFORE YOUR
CUSTOMERS CATCH
YOUR STOMACH FLU

00:44.208 --> 00:45.583
AND WE HAVE
TO RENAME
THE RESTAURANT

00:45.583 --> 00:47.208
LEERY'S PENDING
LAWSUIT.

00:48.208 --> 00:49.458
HE'S RIGHT.

00:49.458 --> 00:53.250
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.
I GIVE UP.

00:55.750 --> 00:56.750
SHE PROMISED ME
SHE'D GO

00:56.750 --> 00:57.792
TO THE DOCTOR
LAST WEEK.

00:57.792 --> 00:59.208
I THOUGHT SHE HAD
THE SAME THING YOU HAD.

00:59.208 --> 01:00.291
YOURS DIDN'T
KEEP COMING BACK.

01:00.291 --> 01:02.917
GUYS, GALE'S BEEN
THROWING UP A LOT, RIGHT?

01:02.917 --> 01:05.375
AND SHE'S STILL HUNGRY
AND PUTTING ON SOME WEIGHT?

01:05.375 --> 01:06.834
SHE'S TIRED ALL THE TIME?
HER BACK HURTS?

01:06.834 --> 01:10.000
IRRITABILITY, MOOD SWINGS?

01:10.000 --> 01:12.417
YEAH.
THE WORST.
HOW'D YOU KNOW?

01:12.417 --> 01:16.083
SOUNDS TO ME LIKE SHE'LL
BE FEELING A LOT BETTER
IN ABOUT 9 MONTHS.

01:26.375 --> 01:27.583
WHAT?

02:23.458 --> 02:24.708
HOW'S IT GOING IN THERE?

02:24.708 --> 02:26.625
Gale: I CAN'T
CONCENTRATE WITH YOU
TALKING OUT THERE

02:26.625 --> 02:28.041
ABOUT WHAT I'M DOING
IN HERE.

02:30.708 --> 02:32.959
OK, NOW IT'S
WAY TOO QUIET.

02:32.959 --> 02:34.959
UH, DAWSON, UM,
SO HAVE YOU STARTED

02:34.959 --> 02:37.458
STUDYING FOR
YOUR S.A.T.s, YET?

02:37.458 --> 02:41.125
TOOK THE S.A.T.s. TWICE.

02:41.125 --> 02:43.291
I KNEW THAT.

02:47.834 --> 02:51.125
IT'S PINK.

02:55.125 --> 02:56.792
Mitch: ALL RIGHT.

02:56.792 --> 02:58.125
ALL RIGHT. FIRST THING
WE DO IS, UH,

02:58.125 --> 03:01.125
WE GET YOU TO
A DOCTOR A.S.A.P.
TO CONFIRM YOUR RESULTS

03:01.125 --> 03:02.750
AND MAKE SURE
EVERYTHING'S OK.

03:02.750 --> 03:04.500
WHERE YOU GOING?

03:04.500 --> 03:08.834
UH, I'M LATE. IT'S MY FIRST DAY
PAINTING MR. BROOKS' HOUSE.

03:08.834 --> 03:10.834
WELL, AREN'T YOU
GOING TO SAY
ANYTHING FIRST?

03:10.834 --> 03:13.333
CONGRATULATIONS.

03:27.000 --> 03:28.375
UH-UH-UH.

03:28.375 --> 03:30.750
WHAT'S WRONG?
WHY'D YOU STOP?

03:30.750 --> 03:33.000
UH, WELL, BECAUSE
EVERY AFTERNOON,

03:33.000 --> 03:36.125
WE SIT OUT HERE
AND WE MAKE OUT, AND THEN
INEVITABLY AT SOME POINT,

03:36.125 --> 03:38.875
YOU STOP US, AND WE JUST
GO INSIDE AND WATCH TV

03:38.875 --> 03:39.917
FOR THE REST
OF THE AFTERNOON.

03:39.917 --> 03:41.375
SO TODAY I'M ISSUING
A PREEMPTIVE STRIKE.

03:41.375 --> 03:43.041
AND I'M ISSUING
A COUNTEROFFENSIVE.

03:43.041 --> 03:46.875
NO, NO. STOP RIGHT THERE.
HAVEN'T YOU EVER HEARD
THE TERM NO MEANS NO?

03:46.875 --> 03:48.125
I DON'T THINK
I'VE EVER
HEARD THAT FROM YOU.

03:48.125 --> 03:49.542
WELL, YOU'RE HEARING IT NOW.

03:52.250 --> 03:56.375
I'M SERIOUS.
IT'S TIME FOR US
TO WATCH SOME TV.

03:58.708 --> 04:01.333
LET ME GET THIS
STRAIGHT.

04:01.333 --> 04:02.959
YOUR GIRLFRIEND
OFFERS YOU HER LIPS

04:02.959 --> 04:06.458
IN THE SPIRIT OF TEENAGE
LUST, AND YOU'D RATHER
SIT HERE AND WATCH

04:06.458 --> 04:09.792
THE E! TRUE HOLLYWOOD
STORY  ON DANNY BONADUCE
FOR THE FOURTH TIME?

04:09.792 --> 04:11.083
YOU ALWAYS GET TO STOP IT.

04:11.083 --> 04:14.125
AND I NEVER GET TO STOP IT.
SO TODAY, I'M STOPPING IT.

04:14.125 --> 04:15.542
STOP IT, PACEY.

04:15.542 --> 04:16.458
I JUST DID.

04:16.458 --> 04:17.125
YOU KNOW
WHAT I MEAN.

04:17.125 --> 04:20.083
AND YOU KNOW HOW I FEEL.

04:20.083 --> 04:21.541
ARE WE HAVING
A FIGHT?

04:21.541 --> 04:23.708
WELL, NOT TO THE BEST
OF MY KNOWLEDGE.

04:25.500 --> 04:27.208
FEELS LIKE ONE
OF THOSE TIMES

04:27.208 --> 04:29.083
WHEN YOU SAY
THAT YOU'RE
KIDDING AROUND,

04:29.083 --> 04:30.417
BUT REALLY,
WE'RE HAVING
A FIGHT, PACE.

04:30.417 --> 04:33.583
I ASSURE YOU, EVERYTHING IS
PERFECTLY ALL RIGHT.

04:36.959 --> 04:39.083
HOW DID I GET MYSELF
INTO THIS?

04:39.083 --> 04:41.750
I WAS
A MEDIOCRE SOCCER PLAYER
BACK IN JUNIOR HIGH.

04:41.750 --> 04:43.125
I KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT KIDS.

04:43.125 --> 04:44.875
I'VE NEVER COACHED
ANYTHING IN MY LIFE.

04:44.875 --> 04:50.500
COME ON, COACHING PEEWEE SOCCER
IS A GREAT OPPORTUNITY
TO HELP MOLD YOUNG MINDS,

04:50.500 --> 04:53.792
TEACH THEM ABOUT TEAMWORK
AND SPORTSMANSHIP.

04:53.792 --> 04:56.834
OK. THE ONLY REASON TO DO IT
IS BECAUSE IT LOOKS GOOD

04:56.834 --> 04:58.583
ON YOUR COLLEGE APPS.

04:58.583 --> 05:02.125
BUT DON'T WORRY. I TAKE
FULL RESPONSIBILITY SHOULD IT
TURN OUT TO BE DISASTROUS.

05:02.125 --> 05:03.500
DAMN STRAIGHT.

05:05.625 --> 05:09.083
OH! HEY, KIDS.
I'M ANDIE,

05:09.083 --> 05:10.959
AND THIS IS
MY BROTHER JACK.

05:10.959 --> 05:13.458
AND TOGETHER,
WE ARE ALL
ABOUT TO EMBARK UPON

05:13.458 --> 05:16.625
A SOCCER EXPERIENCE
THAT WILL ENRICH

05:16.625 --> 05:17.792
YOUR LIVES
FOR YEARS TO COME.

05:17.792 --> 05:20.208
Kids: OHH.

05:20.208 --> 05:23.834
OK. EVERYBODY WHO
WANTS TO HAVE SOME FUN,
RAISE THEIR HANDS.

05:27.500 --> 05:28.750
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

05:28.750 --> 05:30.792
HER NAME
IS MOLLY,
COACH JACK.

05:30.792 --> 05:31.542
MOLLY.

05:31.542 --> 05:33.417
YOU DON'T WANT TO TALK, MOLLY?

05:33.417 --> 05:34.333
HOW COME?

05:34.333 --> 05:35.875
'CAUSE SHE
HATES SOCCER.

05:35.875 --> 05:37.875
SHUT UP.

05:37.875 --> 05:40.583
SHE HATES SOCCER.
WHY DO YOU HATE SOCCER, MOLLY?

05:42.250 --> 05:44.125
OK. YOU DON'T WANT TO TALK,
THAT'S FINE.

05:44.125 --> 05:46.166
YOU DON'T HAVE TO TALK
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO TALK.

05:46.166 --> 05:48.041
GEE, THANKS.

05:48.041 --> 05:50.959
I HEARD SOMETHING.
I THINK SHE TALKED.

05:50.959 --> 05:53.333
ANYWAY, WHAT MOLLY
DOESN'T KNOW IS THAT
BY THE END OF THE SEASON,

05:53.333 --> 05:56.500
NO ONE IS
GOING TO HATE SOCCER,

05:56.500 --> 05:58.166
'CAUSE WE'RE GOING TO HAVE
SO MUCH FUN

05:58.166 --> 06:01.875
RUNNIN' AROUND, WINNING SOME
GAMES, AND EATING PLENTY
OF PIZZA AFTERWARDS.

06:01.875 --> 06:02.875
SO WHO'S WITH ME?

06:02.875 --> 06:04.458
Kids: ME! YEAH!

06:10.750 --> 06:13.667
I THINK YOU HAVE THAT SPACE
COVERED, MR. LEERY.

06:13.667 --> 06:16.458
UNLESS YOU'D LIKE TO BE
WORKING OFF YOUR DEBT
INTO THE NEXT MILLENNIUM.

06:16.458 --> 06:17.708
SORRY ABOUT THAT,
MR. BROOKS.

06:17.708 --> 06:21.750
WHAT MIGHT BE PROMPTING
SUCH A DISTRACTED PERFORMANCE?

06:21.750 --> 06:24.583
WORRIED WHICH POMPOM GIRL
TO ASK TO THE PEP RALLY?

06:24.583 --> 06:27.041
MIGHT I REMIND YOU THAT
ALTHOUGH I'M NOT PAYING YOU,

06:27.041 --> 06:28.333
IT IS YOU WHO OWES ME
THE DEBT OF SERVICE.

06:28.333 --> 06:31.000
SO I SUGGEST YOU WORK IT OFF
TO THE BEST OF YOUR ABILITY

06:31.000 --> 06:34.333
AND LEAVE THE JUVENILE ANGST
ON THE PLAYGROUND
WHERE IT BELONGS.

06:34.333 --> 06:35.834
WILL DO, MR. BROOKS.

06:35.834 --> 06:41.125
WELL, WELL, WHAT'S THIS?
FANCY YOURSELF A PHOTOGRAPHER,
AN ARTISTE?

06:41.125 --> 06:42.375
LET'S HAVE A LOOK AT THESE.

06:42.375 --> 06:44.375
COULD YOU LEAVE
MY PERSONAL PROPERTY
ALONE, PLEASE?

06:44.375 --> 06:46.208
SURELY THE BOY WHO STOLE
AND WRECKED MY BOAT

06:46.208 --> 06:49.333
IS NOT GIVING ME
A LECTURE ON THE SANCTITY
OF PERSONAL PROPERTY?

06:49.333 --> 06:50.792
PEDESTRIAN.

06:50.792 --> 06:51.792
WHOLLY UNINTERESTING.

06:51.792 --> 06:57.875
AMATEURISH AND
TERRIBLE COMPOSITION, TOO.

06:57.875 --> 06:59.792
YOU--YOU DIDN'T
TAKE THIS ON PURPOSE?

07:01.792 --> 07:03.500
WHEW!

07:04.625 --> 07:05.834
AS A PHOTOGRAPHER,

07:05.834 --> 07:08.250
YOU'RE A MEDIOCRE
HOUSE PAINTER, MR. LEERY.

07:08.250 --> 07:09.542
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT YOUR PROBLEM IS?

07:09.542 --> 07:11.250
THOSE PHOTOS
ARE COLD, UNEMOTIONAL.

07:11.250 --> 07:13.917
THERE IS NO SPARK.

07:13.917 --> 07:15.708
THANK YOU
FOR THE COGENT
ANALYSIS.

07:15.708 --> 07:17.583
I WILL KEEP THAT
IN MIND NEXT TIME.

07:22.959 --> 07:24.625
HEY, THERE.

07:26.542 --> 07:27.417
WELL, LOOKS LIKE
WE WERE BOTH ROBBED

07:27.417 --> 07:29.625
ON THAT
HISTORY TEST.

07:29.625 --> 07:31.917
"B-", MY ASS.

07:31.917 --> 07:32.667
WHAT DID YOU GET?

07:35.041 --> 07:37.792
I THINK
I SET THE CURVE.

07:37.792 --> 07:39.125
WELL, I CAN SEE
HOW THAT WOULD BE
AGGRAVATING.

07:39.125 --> 07:42.583
[GIGGLES]
JEEZ!

07:45.250 --> 07:48.333
WHAT'S WRONG?

07:48.333 --> 07:50.750
NOTHING.

07:50.750 --> 07:52.166
MASHED POTATOES
ARE COLD.

07:52.166 --> 07:54.083
I GOT YOU.
SO, IT'S JUST BEEN
ONE TRAGEDY

07:54.083 --> 07:55.917
AFTER ANOTHER
TODAY, HUH?

07:57.625 --> 08:00.125
MASHED POTATOES ARE COLD,
AND SO AM I.

08:00.125 --> 08:02.417
IS THIS ABOUT SEX?

08:02.417 --> 08:03.625
IS IT THAT OBVIOUS?

08:03.625 --> 08:06.125
HEH! NO, NOT REALLY.
IT'S JUST--

08:06.125 --> 08:07.583
IT'S JUST THAT
IT ALWAYS IS.

08:10.250 --> 08:13.291
I THINK PACEY
IS STARTING
TO GET IMPATIENT.

08:13.291 --> 08:15.583
JOEY, HE LOVES YOU.
HE'LL WAIT.

08:15.583 --> 08:16.750
BUT, JEN,

08:16.750 --> 08:18.667
PACEY'S NOT THE PROBLEM.

08:18.667 --> 08:21.000
IT'S ME.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.875
I MEAN, LET'S FACE IT.
THE WAITING JUST GOES
ON AND ON,

08:22.875 --> 08:25.875
AND AT THIS POINT,
EVEN I'M GETTING
IMPATIENT,

08:25.875 --> 08:28.834
BUT...FOR SOME REASON,
I JUST KEEP WAITING.

08:28.834 --> 08:29.959
JOEY, LET ME
ASK YOU SOMETHING.

08:29.959 --> 08:31.625
ARE YOU SURE
THAT YOU REALLY
WANNA HAVE SEX?

08:31.625 --> 08:33.332
OF COURSE
I WANNA HAVE SEX.

08:33.332 --> 08:35.875
THE QUESTION IS
AM I READY?

08:35.875 --> 08:39.375
BECAUSE I DON'T KNOW
HOW YOU KNOW. I MEAN...

08:39.375 --> 08:40.500
EVERYONE JUST SAYS
THAT YOU JUST KNOW,

08:40.500 --> 08:43.500
BUT WHAT IF THAT'S
JUST WHAT THEY SAY

08:43.500 --> 08:45.208
AND THEY NEVER
REALLY KNOW?

08:45.208 --> 08:46.667
JOEY, I THINK
THAT YOU'D FEEL
MORE READY

08:46.667 --> 08:47.291
IF YOU WERE
ACTUALLY PREPARED.

08:47.291 --> 08:49.458
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

08:49.458 --> 08:50.542
LISTEN...FOR GIRLS
IN NEW YORK,

08:50.542 --> 08:51.583
A VISIT
TO THE FREE CLINIC

08:51.583 --> 08:55.041
TO GET
BIRTH CONTROL,
SAFE-SEX ADVICE--

08:55.041 --> 08:56.250
IT'S A RITE
OF PASSAGE.

08:56.250 --> 08:57.417
IT'S LIKE GETTING
A BAT MITZVAH

08:57.417 --> 08:59.208
OR, YOU KNOW,
YOUR LEARNER'S
PERMIT TEST.

08:59.208 --> 09:00.417
THE FREE CLINIC.

09:00.417 --> 09:02.333
YEAH.

09:02.333 --> 09:04.041
THE TRUTH IS
I DON'T THINK

09:04.041 --> 09:05.125
THAT ANYBODY
EVER REALLY KNOWS
IF THEY'RE READY,

09:05.125 --> 09:07.875
BUT YOU DO KNOW
IF YOU'RE PREPARED,

09:07.875 --> 09:10.208
AND YOU'RE NOT.

09:10.208 --> 09:12.208
YOU'RE RIGHT.

09:12.208 --> 09:14.333
TO RESPONSIBLE
SEXUAL GRATIFICATION.

09:18.041 --> 09:19.750
TO WOMANHOOD.

09:19.750 --> 09:21.125
CHEERS.

09:25.834 --> 09:27.083
YOU OK?

09:27.083 --> 09:29.667
I'M FINE.

09:29.667 --> 09:33.458
LOOK, I'VE BEEN
THINKING ABOUT IT.

09:33.458 --> 09:35.708
I KNOW
THIS IS TERRIFYING.

09:35.708 --> 09:38.375
THERE'S SO MANY CARDS
STACKED AGAINST US,

09:38.375 --> 09:40.291
BUT IT'S GONNA BE OK.

09:41.125 --> 09:43.375
AND DON'T WORRY
ABOUT DAWSON.

09:43.375 --> 09:45.708
HE'S JUST SHOCKED,
BUT HE'LL BE FINE.

09:45.708 --> 09:46.750
IT'S A GOOD SHOCK.

09:49.375 --> 09:51.875
NOW, MITCH, HAVE YOU
THOUGHT AT ALL

09:51.875 --> 09:54.500
ABOUT HOW WE CAN POSSIBLY
SEND DAWSON TO COLLEGE

09:54.500 --> 09:57.917
AND  RAISE
ANOTHER CHILD?

09:57.917 --> 09:59.959
WE'RE ALREADY IN DEBT
AS IT IS.

09:59.959 --> 10:00.959
AND WHAT ABOUT THE FACT

10:00.959 --> 10:02.875
WE'RE NOT EXACTLY
25-YEAR-OLDS ANYMORE?

10:02.875 --> 10:04.208
DO WE EVEN HAVE
THE STAMINA

10:04.208 --> 10:06.917
TO BE PARENTS
ALL OVER AGAIN?

10:06.917 --> 10:08.417
THAT'S 20 MORE YEARS

10:08.417 --> 10:12.125
THAT WE WOULD
HAVE TO COMMIT
TO ANOTHER CHILD.

10:12.125 --> 10:14.250
NOT TO MENTION
WHAT WE PUT DAWSON THROUGH

10:14.250 --> 10:16.166
THESE PAST FEW YEARS.

10:16.166 --> 10:17.667
WHAT IF THAT
HAPPENS AGAIN?

10:17.667 --> 10:20.250
THAT'S NOT GONNA
HAPPEN AGAIN.

10:20.250 --> 10:21.917
I DON'T KNOW.
I CAN'T HELP THINKING

10:21.917 --> 10:23.834
THAT WE SHOULD HAVE
THOUGHT ABOUT THIS BEFORE.

10:23.834 --> 10:26.917
MAYBE THAT'S TRUE...

10:26.917 --> 10:28.917
BUT YOU'RE
PREGNANT NOW.

10:28.917 --> 10:30.792
I MEAN,
THAT'S THE REALITY.

10:30.792 --> 10:33.125
UM...

10:33.125 --> 10:36.959
MITCH, YOU'RE
AVOIDING ONE THING.

10:36.959 --> 10:39.291
JUST BECAUSE
I'M PREGNANT
DOESN'T MEAN

10:39.291 --> 10:42.291
THAT I HAVE TO STAY
THAT WAY.

10:42.291 --> 10:46.083
AND IF I WERE
TO MAKE THAT DECISION
RIGHT THIS SECOND...

10:49.792 --> 10:51.792
I WOULDN'T.

11:03.625 --> 11:04.291
HEY, GUYS.

11:04.291 --> 11:05.959
SO TRAGIC.

11:05.959 --> 11:08.166
ALL THESE ADULTS
PUSHING THEIR KIDS
OUT ONTO THE FIELD

11:08.166 --> 11:11.333
IN ORDER TO MAKE
ONE LAST GRASP
AT VICARIOUS GLORY.

11:11.333 --> 11:13.417
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

11:13.417 --> 11:17.000
I'M CAROLINE,
BY THE WAY.
CAROLINE SAY.

11:17.000 --> 11:18.458
MOLLY'S OLDER SISTER.

11:18.458 --> 11:20.667
MOM HAD ME
WHEN SHE WAS 21,

11:20.667 --> 11:21.291
MOLLY WHEN SHE WAS 40.

11:21.291 --> 11:23.500
MM-HMM.

11:23.500 --> 11:26.417
THAT WOULD MAKE ME 28,
IN CASE YOU WERE WONDERING.

11:26.417 --> 11:28.542
GOTCHA.

11:28.542 --> 11:30.208
AND HOW OLD
WOULD THAT MAKE YOU?

11:30.208 --> 11:31.500
I'M 18.

11:31.500 --> 11:33.083
HMM.

11:34.667 --> 11:36.375
GIRLFRIEND?

11:36.375 --> 11:37.834
UH, SISTER.

11:37.834 --> 11:39.875
OH. COOL.

11:39.875 --> 11:41.792
HEH HEH HEH.

11:41.792 --> 11:43.834
COACH JACK,
AM I MAKING YOU
UNCOMFORTABLE?

11:43.834 --> 11:46.917
[LAUGHS] NO.
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

11:46.917 --> 11:48.208
OH, I JUST THOUGHT
MAYBE YOU THOUGHT

11:48.208 --> 11:49.458
I WAS FLIRTING
OR SOMETHING.

11:49.458 --> 11:50.542
FLIRTING? WHY--
WHY WOULD I THINK
YOU'RE FLIRTING?

11:50.542 --> 11:52.917
BECAUSE I AM
FLIRTING.

11:52.917 --> 11:56.000
HEH! UM...
CAROLINE?

11:56.000 --> 11:57.083
MM-HMM?

11:57.083 --> 11:59.041
UH, LOOK,
I-I'M FLATTERED
AND EVERYTHING,

11:59.041 --> 12:00.208
BUT, UH--

12:00.208 --> 12:01.375
I'M COMING ON
TOO STRONG.

12:01.375 --> 12:03.500
AND YOU'RE SHY.

12:03.500 --> 12:05.000
YEAH, SEE, I--I AM.

12:05.000 --> 12:06.667
I'M SHY AND--
AND I'M--

12:06.667 --> 12:07.333
SHY AND WHAT?

12:07.333 --> 12:09.667
SHY AND...

12:09.667 --> 12:12.708
ALL RIGHT, YOU MULL
THAT ONE OVER,

12:12.708 --> 12:15.250
AND I'LL JUST BE SEEING
YOUR SWEET FACE TOMORROW.

12:15.250 --> 12:17.333
UNTIL THEN,

12:17.333 --> 12:18.875
AU REVOIR,
COACH JACK.

12:28.166 --> 12:29.583
THAT OLD MAN
IS CLEARLY NUTS.

12:29.583 --> 12:32.041
THESE ARE GREAT,
DAWSON.

12:32.041 --> 12:33.792
ACTUALLY,
HE'S RIGHT.
THEY SUCK.

12:33.792 --> 12:35.625
NO, THEY MOST DEFINITELY
DO NOT SUCK.

12:35.625 --> 12:37.417
OH, IT'S OK.
[SHUTTER CLICKS]

12:37.417 --> 12:39.917
ONE HAS TO SUCK
BEFORE YOU CAN
STOP SUCKING.

12:39.917 --> 12:42.750
TRUE GENIUS BEGINS
IN MEDIOCRITY.

12:42.750 --> 12:44.583
WELL, I APPRECIATE
THE HUMBLE ARTIST BIT.

12:44.583 --> 12:47.417
IT'S WAY PREFERABLE
TO SELF-DESCRIBED GENIUS.

12:47.417 --> 12:51.667
BUT EVEN YOU CANNOT DENY
YOUR NATURAL ABILITIES.

12:51.667 --> 12:53.417
