LOOK AT ME, THEY SEE
SOMETHING AWFUL.

39:42.583 --> 39:44.208
DO YOU KNOW
HOW THAT FEELS?

39:44.208 --> 39:47.208
GIVE IT TIME.
IT WILL BLOW OVER, I SWEAR.

39:47.208 --> 39:49.291
NAH, IT NEVER DOES.

39:49.291 --> 39:51.291
IT WILL.

39:55.542 --> 40:00.667
DO YOU MIND IF I,
UM, FINISH UP ALONE?

40:00.667 --> 40:02.417
YOU SURE?

40:02.417 --> 40:03.417
YEAH.

40:03.417 --> 40:04.959
OK.

40:18.959 --> 40:20.458
EACH TIME I STEP OUT
ONTO THIS PORCH

40:20.458 --> 40:23.208
TO WATCH YOU AT WORK,
MR. LEERY,

40:23.208 --> 40:25.750
I BREATHE A SIGH
OF RELIEF THAT
I'M NOT PAYING YOU.

40:25.750 --> 40:29.166
THIS WAY, I CAN STILL
HIRE A PROFESSIONAL
TO PAINT OVER YOUR MESS.

40:29.166 --> 40:32.208
YOU KNOW, MR. BROOKS,
I ACTUALLY THINK I'M
DOING A PRETTY GOOD JOB.

40:32.208 --> 40:35.417
WE ALL HAVE
OUR ILLUSIONS.

40:35.417 --> 40:39.041
AH, I SEE YOU'VE BEEN
HARD AT WORK ADDING
TO YOUR COLLECTION.

40:39.041 --> 40:43.375
AH, TRITE.

40:43.375 --> 40:45.875
A NAKED ATTEMPT
TO EVOKE SENTIMENT.

40:45.875 --> 40:48.750
WHY NOT JUST SHOOT
A PHOTO OF A PUPPY
IN GARBAGE CAN, HUH?

40:50.792 --> 40:51.750
HMM.

40:54.500 --> 40:58.083
"HMM"? THAT'S THE BEST
SCATHING CRITICISM
YOU CAN MUSTER?

40:58.083 --> 41:00.917
SOMETIMES HONESTY
IS SCATHING, DAWSON.
I CAN'T HELP THAT.

41:00.917 --> 41:03.458
BUT THIS LAST ONE...
AH...

41:03.458 --> 41:06.125
THIS LAST ONE
IS ACTUALLY NOT BAD.

41:06.125 --> 41:10.792
IT'S THE FIRST PICTURE
THAT MAKES A CONNECTION
WITH THE SUBJECT,

41:10.792 --> 41:15.458
AS IF YOU'RE NOT ONLY
SHOOTING HER MELANCHOLY
BUT YOUR OWN.

41:15.458 --> 41:17.667
THIS IS THE FIRST ONE
I'VE SEEN WITH A BIT
OF YOU IN IT.

41:19.125 --> 41:20.792
THIS ONE HAS POTENTIAL.

41:22.917 --> 41:26.458
I DON'T SEE YOU
PAINTING, MR. LEERY.

41:29.125 --> 41:30.333
[DOOR SHUTS]
